Provenance
================================================================================

EAP has no third-party runtime dependencies and no Elastic-License (ELv2)
source. Most code is original; some documentation and helpers are MIT-licensed
derivatives of the upstream projects below, whose copyright and permission
notices are retained verbatim in docs/legal/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md.

The following projects are credited (concepts, and — where marked — MIT
documentation/code derivatives whose notices are retained):

  * graphify  — https://github.com/Graphify-Labs/graphify  — MIT
    EAP-Context is an independent, standard-library-only symbol-graph engine
    whose design is informed by graphify's code-graph approach. No graphify
    source and none of its dependencies (tree-sitter, networkx, numpy, etc.)
    are used.

  * context-mode — https://github.com/mksglu/context-mode — Elastic License 2.0
    EAP-Runtime is an independent clean-room reimplementation of the general
    context-offload pattern (also seen in OpenAI Code Interpreter and
    Anthropic's "code execution with MCP"). It contains NO context-mode source.

  * caveman (MIT, Julius Brussee), TLDR (MIT, ZeroPointNineBar), ponytail (MIT, Dietrich
    Gebert) — EAP-Signal descends from TLDR (which credits caveman); EAP-Lean is
    a documentation + examples/bench derivative of ponytail (MIT ports). EAP does
    not vendor ponytail's hook runtime (reimplemented under src/hooks/).

See docs/legal/ATTRIBUTION.md for the full record and the clean-room guard.
